    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-29T08:16:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-29T08:16:00-05:00" n="212"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d212">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/1009</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Roumania</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_VCJ1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Vopicka</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Bucharest</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-29T15:00:00+01:44">
                        <hi rend="italic">September 29, 1914, 3 p.m.</hi>
                    </date>
                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 5:40 p.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>Referring to my cable of September 14, noon.<note n="1" xml:id="d212fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_106">p. 106</ref>.</note> It
                    appears probable that, as a result of Crown Council which is to be held next
                    Wednesday, war will be declared by Roumania against Germany and Austria-Hungary.
                    Great popular demonstrations are held here daily in favor of such action.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_VCJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vopicka</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
